@defvr {Customisable Variable} package_BUILD_VERSION
A special version specification to tag binary distribution packages.  It
should be used to give a version to the package file.

It defaults to @code{1nau}, which means ``Nausicaa build version 1''.
@end defvr


@defvr {Customisable Variable} package_ARCH
Architecture specification to be used to tag binary distribution
packages.  It should be used to identify the architecture for which a
package file was built.

It must be set to a meaningful value, like @code{i486} or @code{i686}.
It defaults to @code{noarch}, which means that the package holds only
architecture independent files (like source and documentation files).
@end defvr


@defvar package_NAME
@defvarx package_VERSION
These are aliases for @code{PACKAGE_NAME} and @code{PACKAGE_VERSION},
and are used to compose the name of binary distribution files.
@end defvar


@defvar package_PREFIX
The file name of binary distribution packages, without extension.  It
is set to:

@example
$(package_NAME)-$(package_VERSION)-$(package_ARCH)-$(package_BUILD_VERSION)
@end example

As a usage example, Slackware packages have name:

@example
$(package_PREFIX).tgz
@end example
@end defvar


